wikipedia_page.main: Alfred George Ernest Tasker (born 16 June 1934 in Southwark, London) was an English first-class cricketer who played in one match, keeping wicket for Worcestershire against Cambridge University in 1956. He took one catch, to dismiss future Test player Bob Barber, but Worcestershire declared in both their innings before he had a chance to bat; he never did get an opportunity.
